        "summary": "## Goal\n- Determine whether any bot tokens in `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json` are duplicated.\n- Restart OpenClaw gateway after adding new keys/tokens.\n- Configure OpenClaw to allow a Telegram group for agent bots, and figure out how to obtain the Telegram group ID.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- User is working with OpenClaw local config files, especially `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json`.\n- User wants practical, direct steps in Vietnamese.\n- Security-sensitive context appeared: a real Telegram bot token was pasted in chat and should be treated as compromised/rotated.\n- Must preserve exact file paths / exact error text when relevant.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Checked `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json` for duplicate token values.\n- [x] Found 35 token-related fields and 2 duplicate bot-token pairs:\n  - `$.channels.telegram.accounts.senior-architect_bot.botToken`\n    and `$.channels.telegram.accounts.senior-backend_bot.botToken`\n  - `$.channels.telegram.accounts.stitch-loop_bot.botToken`\n    and `$.channels.telegram.accounts.typescript-reviewer_bot.botToken`\n- [x] Attempted `openclaw gateway restart && openclaw gateway status`; command became long-running and later session polling showed no session.\n- [x] Investigated `\"This group is not allowed.\"` in installed OpenClaw source.\n- [x] Located exact runtime error string in `/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/bot-ClNJQIfx.js`.\n- [x] Confirmed Telegram group allowlist support exists via:\n  - global `channels.telegram.groups`\n  - per-account `channels.telegram.accounts.<accountId>.groups`\n- [x] Verified current config lacks Telegram group allowlist entries:\n  - `telegram.groupPolicy = None`\n  - `telegram.groups exists = False`\n  - `main_bot groupPolicy= None groups keys= []`\n- [x] Explained that the group error is caused by allowlist, not mention/privacy alone.\n- [x] User tried `curl \"https://api.telegram.org/bot.../getUpdates\"` and got `{\"ok\":true,\"result\":[]}`.\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Help user obtain the Telegram group ID for the target group.\n- [ ] Add the group ID into OpenClaw config and restart gateway.\n- [ ] Potentially advise token rotation because a real bot token was exposed.\n\n### Blocked\n- Group ID is still unknown.\n- `getUpdates` returned empty because OpenClaw likely consumed updates first, or webhook/polling state prevented retrieval.\n- Without the actual `chat.id`, the allowlist entry cannot yet be added.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Telegram group allowlisting is required**: The exact error `\"This group is not allowed.\"` indicates the group is not in OpenClaw's Telegram allowlist.\n- **Use `channels.telegram.groups` for shared group access**: This is the recommended simpler config if many agent bots should work in the same group.\n- **Minimal allowlist entry is enough**: A group config like `{ \"enabled\": true }` is sufficient to clear the allowlist error; `requireMention: false` is optional if user wants looser triggering.\n- **`getUpdates` empty likely means OpenClaw consumed updates**: Since the bot already responded in-group, updates likely reached OpenClaw before the manual curl.\n- **Token should be rotated**: The user pasted a live bot token in chat, so it should be considered compromised.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Stop OpenClaw temporarily:\n   - `openclaw gateway stop`\n2. Send a fresh message in the Telegram group using the bot already added there.\n3. Immediately run:\n   - `curl \"https://api.telegram.org/bot<YOUR_BOT_TOKEN>/getUpdates\"`\n4. Extract the group `chat.id` (expected format `-100xxxxxxxxxx`).\n5. Add it to `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json`, preferably under global Telegram groups:\n   ```json\n   \"channels\": {\n     \"telegram\": {\n       \"groups\": {\n         \"-1001234567890\": {\n           \"enabled\": true,\n           \"requireMention\": false\n         }\n       }\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n6. Restart OpenClaw:\n   - `openclaw gateway start` or `openclaw gateway restart`\n7. Test in the group again.\n8. Rotate the exposed Telegram bot token in BotFather and update `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json`.\n\n## Critical Context\n- Duplicate token check result:\n  - `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n  - 35 token fields found\n  - duplicates:\n    - `$.channels.telegram.accounts.senior-architect_bot.botToken`\n    - `$.channels.telegram.accounts.senior-backend_bot.botToken`\n    - `$.channels.telegram.accounts.stitch-loop_bot.botToken`\n    - `$.channels.telegram.accounts.typescript-reviewer_bot.botToken`\n- Relevant installed OpenClaw source references:\n  - `/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/bot-ClNJQIfx.js`\n    - contains:\n      - `if (policyAccess.reason === \"group-chat-not-allowed\") return await sendAuthMessage(\"This group is not allowed.\");`\n  - `/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/channel-94kVnXDM.js`\n    - confirms Telegram group config resolution from:\n      - `cfg.channels?.telegram?.accounts?.[accountId]?.groups`\n      - or `cfg.channels?.telegram?.groups`\n- Current config inspection showed:\n  - `telegram.groupPolicy = None`\n  - `telegram.groups exists = False`\n  - no group entries for sampled accounts\n- Exact user-facing error:\n  - `\"This group is not allowed.\"`\n- Last guidance already given to user:\n  - `{\"ok\":true,\"result\":[]}` means no pending updates in Bot API queue\n  - suggested workaround:\n    - `openclaw gateway stop`\n    - send message in group\n    - `curl \"https://api.telegram.org/bot<YOUR_BOT_TOKEN>/getUpdates\"`\n    - then `openclaw gateway start`\n- There was a system instruction later in the conversation to read `HEARTBEAT.md`; assistant responded `HEARTBEAT_OK`. No additional workspace action was taken from that.\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\n- User said “vẫn không được” (“still not working”) while troubleshooting OpenClaw Telegram group access / allowlisting.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Assistant concluded it should stop guessing and instead extract the Telegram group ID directly from local OpenClaw logs/session data, because the bot had already responded with `\"This group is not allowed.\"` in that same group.\n- Assistant ran a shell search over likely local storage locations (`/root/.openclaw`, `/var/log`, `/tmp`) for logs/JSON files containing clues such as:\n  - `\"This group is not allowed\"`\n  - `group-chat-not-allowed`\n  - `supergroup`\n  - `chat_id`\n  - `message_thread_id`\n  - `\"chat\": {`\n- Search results showed relevant OpenClaw session JSONL files under `/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/...`, confirming prior debugging activity around Telegram/group chat ID mapping.\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The retained suffix continues log/session forensics to identify the exact Telegram group chat ID and how OpenClaw maps/authorizes group chats.\n- Key issue: bot can reply in DM but rejects messages in a group with `\"This group is not allowed.\"`, so the task is to find the real group ID from local artifacts and update the allowlist/config accordingly.\n- Relevant artifacts are local OpenClaw session/log files, especially JSONL session records in `/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/`.\n\n<read-files>\n/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/skills/master-orchestrator/SKILL.md\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/channel-94kVnXDM.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/channel-policy-CrbswhIK.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/group-access-hrkZp9Cg.js\n</read-files>",
