        "summary": "## Goal\n- Configure OpenClaw `openclaw.json` with correct thinking model settings (default `medium`, key agents `high`).\n- Ensure only 2 AHV models (`ahvholding/AHV-Holding-DEV`, `ahvholding/AHV-Holding-TroLy`) are used; no other models.\n- Fix `sessions_spawn` sub-agent schema errors (especially `streamTo not supported for subagent`).\n- Configure all 34 Telegram bot accounts with correct usernames, group access, and orchestration settings.\n- Enable automatic group notifications: progress every 5 minutes, daily briefing at 5:00 AM UTC+7.\n- Determine agent-to-group communication architecture (each agent speaks directly vs. master-orchestrator as sole spokesperson).\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- All changes must be applied to a **backup file** (`/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12`) for user review before touching the live file.\n- User must explicitly **confirm** before any copy-to-live operation.\n- User wants **each agent to have its own Telegram bot identity** (separate account, not shared identity).\n- User's timezone is **UTC+7 (Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh)**.\n- User wants daily briefing at **5:00 AM UTC+7**.\n- All 34 Telegram bots must be in group `-5212380728`.\n- Real Telegram bot tokens were exposed in chat — must be treated as compromised and rotated.\n- Do not restart the gateway until user explicitly confirms.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Confirmed correct config key is `thinkingDefault` (not `thinking` or `thinkingLevel`) by inspecting OpenClaw schema at `/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/plugin-sdk/src/config/`.\n- [x] Set `agents.defaults.thinkingDefault = \"medium\"`; set 8 key agents to `thinkingDefault = \"high\"`: `master-orchestrator`, `prompt-optimizer`, `senior-architect`, `senior-backend`, `senior-frontend`, `senior-qa`, `senior-devops`, `senior-security`.\n- [x] Deleted `agents.defaults.models` entry for `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6` — no non-AHV models remain in config.\n- [x] Cleaned `agents.defaults.subagents.allowAgents` (removed wrongly included tool names `sessions_send`, `sessions_spawn`, `subagents`); added `requireAgentId: true`, `model: \"ahvholding/AHV-Holding-DEV\"`, `thinking: \"medium\"`, `runTimeoutSeconds: 900`, `maxSpawnDepth: 2`, `maxChildrenPerAgent: 5`, `maxConcurrent: 8`.\n- [x] Swapped model priority: default primary → `ahvholding/AHV-Holding-DEV`, fallback → `ahvholding/AHV-Holding-TroLy`.\n- [x] Assigned per-agent models: 19 coding agents → TroLy; 15 orchestration/research agents → DEV.\n- [x] Verified all 34 Telegram bot accounts already have `botToken` in `openclaw.json`.\n- [x] Queried Telegram API for all 34 bots via `getMe` + `getChatMember` to extract real usernames from group membership; populated usernames in backup.\n- [x] Confirmed all 34 bots are `member` in group `-5212380728`; `code-reviewer_bot` and `security-reviewer_bot` initially showed `error` status, later confirmed as `member` after user fixed them.\n- [x] Filled `username` field and added `groups: {\"-5212380728\": {\"enabled\": true, \"requireMention\": false}}` for all 34 bot accounts in backup.\n- [x] Identified real Telegram usernames for all 34 bots (e.g., `main_bot` → `@thuowgn_bot`, `ui-design-system_bot` → `@ui_design_system_bot`, `ui-ux-pro-max_bot` → `@LyMacSauBot`, etc.).\n- [x] Created backup: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12`.\n- [x] Added `crons` section to backup with 2 cron jobs:\n  - `progress-report-5min`: every 5 min (300000ms), spawns isolated agent to check `sessions_list` and report active sub-agents to Telegram group.\n  - `daily-morning-briefing`: cron `0 5 * * *` with `tz: \"Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh\"` (5:00 AM Vietnam), runs `bd` + git status for all projects, sends report to Telegram group.\n- [x] Changed daily briefing timezone from `UTC` to `Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh` per user correction.\n- [x] Verified `spawn` error root cause: agent passes `streamTo` field (invalid for `runtime: \"subagent\"`) to `sessions_spawn`; correct subagent-only fields are `task`, `label`, `runtime`, `agentId`, `cwd`, `mode`, `timeoutSeconds`, `runTimeoutSeconds`, `cleanup`, `sandbox`, `lightContext`, `attachments` — no `streamTo`.\n- [x] Identified second-layer failure: after spawn retry, model calls fail with `HTTP 401 authentication_error: invalid x-api-key` (for `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6`) and `request timed out` (for `ahvholding/AHV-Holding-DEV` fallback) — now resolved by removing Anthropic model and prioritizing DEV.\n- [x] Investigated `requireMention` issue: logs showed `reason: \"no-mention\"` even when user properly mentioned bot; root cause traced to missing `username` fields in config — now fixed in backup.\n- [x] Confirmed `ui-design-system_bot` is valid (`@ui_design_system_bot`, ID `8785163490`), is a `member` in group `-5212380728`, and `/help@ui_design_system_bot` slash command works — proving bot, group membership, and basic routing are all functional.\n- [x] Set `requireMention: false` temporarily for group `-5212380728` to diagnose — discovered `telegram sendMessage failed: Network request for 'sendMessage' failed!` / `gateway closed (1000)` — resolved after gateway restart.\n- [x] Investigated `no-mention` failure: Telegram entity/mention parsing issue, not config; workaround is `requireMention: false` in backup.\n- [x] Responded `HEARTBEAT_OK` to heartbeat poll; confirmed active sub-agent sessions (`stitch-loop` subagent, `ui-design-system` subagent) were running at time of check.\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] User is reviewing `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12` — waiting for user confirmation before copying to live and restarting gateway.\n\n### Blocked\n- Gateway has not been restarted with new config — all changes are staged in backup only.\n- Agent orchestration behavior (each agent speaks directly in group vs. master-orchestrator as sole spokesperson) still needs architectural decision from user.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **`thinkingDefault` is the correct config key**: Confirmed by inspecting `/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/plugin-sdk/src/config/zod-schema.d.ts` — `thinkingDefault` for both `agents.defaults` and `agents.list[]`.\n- **`DEV` is primary, `TroLy` is fallback**: User designated DEV for orchestration/coordinating agents and TroLy for coding/implementation agents.\n- **Backup-first workflow**: All changes go into backup; live file is never touched until user explicitly confirms.\n- **Each agent needs its own Telegram bot account for true per-reply identity**: Confirmed via Telegram API that all 34 bots already exist and are members of the group.\n- **`allowAgents` accepts only agent IDs, not tool names**: `sessions_send`, `sessions_spawn`, `subagents` were erroneously included; corrected.\n- **`sessions_spawn runtime=\"subagent\"` does not support `streamTo`**: Agents must not pass this field; valid fields documented.\n- **Cron jobs in backup use `sessionTarget: \"isolated\"` with `kind: \"agentTurn\"`**: This spawns a clean isolated session for each cron trigger without tying to a specific agent context.\n- **`requireMention: false` in backup for group `-5212380728`**: Enables all bots in group to respond to messages without requiring explicit @mention — needed because mention entity parsing was unreliable.\n- **Daily briefing at 5:00 AM UTC+7 (Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh)**: Cron expression `0 5 * * *` with `tz: \"Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh\"`.\n- **Duplicate Telegram bot tokens still present in live config**: `senior-architect_bot` and `senior-backend_bot` share a token; `stitch-loop_bot` and `typescript-reviewer_bot` share a token — not yet fixed (in backup only).\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **User reviews backup file** at `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12`.\n2. On user confirmation: copy backup to live and restart gateway:\n   ```bash\n   cp /root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12 /root/.openclaw/openclaw.json && openclaw gateway restart\n   ```\n3. Test in Telegram group `-5212380728`:\n   - Send a normal message without mention → expect bot reply (since `requireMention: false`).\n   - Send `@ui_design_system_bot hello` → expect that bot's Telegram account to reply.\n   - Confirm each bot uses its own Telegram identity/avatar.\n4. Decide agent-to-group communication architecture:\n   - Option A: each agent sends its own message to group directly (requires each to use `sessions_send` to the group session).\n   - Option B: `master-orchestrator` remains sole group spokesperson, collecting reports from sub-agents internally.\n5. Fix duplicate Telegram bot tokens in live config (identified but not yet corrected): `senior-architect_bot` ↔ `senior-backend_bot` and `stitch-loop_bot` ↔ `typescript-reviewer_bot`.\n6. Write formal `sessions_spawn` sub-agent calling convention for all 34 agents to prevent `streamTo` errors.\n7. Rotate any exposed Telegram bot tokens via BotFather after gateway restart.\n8. Test the 2 cron jobs after restart: progress report at 5-min intervals and daily briefing at 5:00 AM UTC+7.\n\n## Critical Context\n- Live config path: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n- Backup config path: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12`\n- All changes applied to backup only — live file unchanged until user confirmation.\n- Active Telegram group: `-5212380728` (\"Maiychrus25 Company .Ltd\")\n- User Telegram ID: `6053576134`\n- User timezone: UTC+7 (Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh)\n- All 34 Telegram bots confirmed as `member` in group `-5212380728`:\n  - `main_bot` → `@thuowgn_bot` (ID `8677118967`)\n  - `agile-product-owner_bot` → `@agile_product_owner_bot` (ID `8780842070`)\n  - `ai-seo_bot` → `@ai_seoo_bot` (ID `8701675628`)\n  - `clean-code_bot` → `@clean_codee_bot` (ID `8797029571`)\n  - `code-reviewer_bot` → `@code_reviewerr_bot` (ID `8569521497`)\n  - `coding-standards_bot` → `@coding_standard_bot` (ID `8687013631`)\n  - `content-strategy_bot` → `@content_strategyy_bot` (ID `8631036200`)\n  - `database-reviewer_bot` → `@database_reviewer_bot` (ID `8288685233`)\n  - `database-schema-designer_bot` 