ucceeds → model calls fail with `401 invalid x-api-key` (Anthropic) → fallback timeout (DEV) → pipeline fails.\n- OpenClaw mention-resolution order: inline directive → session override → `agents.list[].thinkingDefault` → `agents.defaults.thinkingDefault` → provider fallback.\n- Correct `sessions_spawn` fields for `runtime: \"subagent\"`: `task`, `label`, `runtime`, `agentId`, `cwd`, `mode`, `timeoutSeconds`, `runTimeoutSeconds`, `cleanup`, `sandbox`, `lightContext`, `attachments`. Fields like `streamTo`, `resumeSessionId`, and ACP-specific fields must not be included.\n- Live config still has duplicate Telegram bot tokens (not yet fixed in backup): `senior-architect_bot` ↔ `senior-backend_bot`; `stitch-loop_bot` ↔ `typescript-reviewer_bot`.\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser (Khương Nịnh) asked to apply/apply changes immediately (`đưa vào áp dụng luôn`), likely referring to applying a configuration backup to the OpenClaw gateway.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Assistant copied backup file (`/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12`) to live config and restarted gateway.\n- Gateway rejected config because `crons` key is not valid at root level.\n- Assistant removed the invalid `crons` key from the backup (it had 2 cron jobs), then re-applied.\n- Gateway then rejected with a new error: Telegram account entries (`username`, `groups` fields) are \"additional properties\" not allowed by the schema.\n- Assistant investigated the schema — found that `groups` IS referenced at the account level in the code, but `username` may not be supported.\n- Confirmed installed OpenClaw version is **2026.4.9**.\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe gateway restart is still failing because Telegram account configs contain `username` and `groups` fields that the current installed OpenClaw version (2026.4.9) doesn't recognize as valid account-level properties. The assistant was investigating whether these fields belong at a different config level or if there's a 