        "summary": "## Goal\n- Configure OpenClaw `openclaw.json` with correct thinking model settings (default `medium`, key agents `high`).\n- Ensure only 2 AHV models (`ahvholding/AHV-Holding-DEV`, `ahvholding/AHV-Holding-TroLy`) are used; no other models.\n- Fix `sessions_spawn` sub-agent schema errors (especially `streamTo not supported for subagent`).\n- Configure all 34 Telegram bot accounts with correct usernames, group access, and orchestration settings.\n- Enable automatic group notifications: progress every 5 minutes, daily briefing at 5:00 AM UTC+7.\n- Determine agent-to-group communication architecture.\n- Get MCP Stitch working end-to-end.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- All changes must be applied to a **backup file** (`/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12`) for user review before touching the live file.\n- User must explicitly **confirm** before any copy-to-live operation.\n- User wants **each agent to have its own Telegram bot identity** (separate account, not shared identity).\n- User's timezone is **UTC+7 (Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh)**.\n- User wants daily briefing at **5:00 AM UTC+7**.\n- All 34 Telegram bots must be in group `-5212380728`.\n- Real Telegram bot tokens were exposed in chat — must be treated as compromised and rotated.\n- Do not restart the gateway until user explicitly confirms.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Confirmed correct config key is `thinkingDefault` (not `thinking` or `thinkingLevel`) by inspecting OpenClaw schema.\n- [x] Set `agents.defaults.thinkingDefault = \"medium\"`; set 8 key agents to `thinkingDefault = \"high\"`.\n- [x] Deleted `agents.defaults.models` entry for `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6` — no non-AHV models remain.\n- [x] Cleaned `agents.defaults.subagents.allowAgents`; configured subagent defaults with `runTimeoutSeconds: 900`, `maxSpawnDepth: 2`, etc.\n- [x] Swapped model priority: default primary → `ahvholding/AHV-Holding-DEV`, fallback → `ahvholding/AHV-Holding-TroLy`.\n- [x] Assigned per-agent models: 19 coding agents → TroLy; 15 orchestration/research agents → DEV.\n- [x] Queried Telegram API for all 34 bots via `getMe` + `getChatMember` to extract real usernames and confirm group membership.\n- [x] Confirmed all 34 bots are `member` in group `-5212380728`.\n- [x] Added `groups: {\"-5212380728\": {\"enabled\": true, \"requireMention\": false}}` for all 34 bot accounts in backup.\n- [x] Changed daily briefing timezone to `Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh`.\n- [x] Created backup: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12`.\n- [x] Identified root cause of `spawn streamTo` errors: agents pass invalid `streamTo` field for `runtime: \"subagent\"`.\n- [x] **`username` field is NOT valid in TelegramAccountConfig schema**: Removed from all 34 account entries in backup.\n- [x] **`crons` key is NOT valid at root level**: Removed from backup.\n- [x] **MCP Stitch root cause identified**: Service account lacked IAM permission for Generative Language API.\n- [x] **User granted Generative Language Service Agent IAM role** to service account `agent-sti@agent-stitch.iam.gserviceaccount.com`.\n- [x] **Confirmed Stitch MCP works via OAuth**: Direct API test — `generate_screen_from_text` returns HTTP 200, 24KB response.\n- [x] **API key approach partially works**: `X-Goog-Api-Key` header works for `tools/list`, `list_projects`, `get_project` ✅. But older key (exposed in prior chat) was revoked.\n- [x] **Created new wrapper `/root/.openclaw/mcp-stitch-key/server.mjs`**: Node.js ESM stdio MCP server that forwards JSON-RPC calls to `https://stitch.googleapis.com/mcp` with API key auth (`X-Goog-Api-Key` header + `?key=` query param). Uses MCP SDK from `stitch-mcp` package's node_modules.\n- [x] **NEW API key tested successfully**: `AQ.Ab8RN6JCkRGaOOCFCgEm4hmzRy2RNmuoMBgzDB_qjHMxrEEruA`\n  - `tools/list` → ✅ 200, returns full 12-tool schema\n  - `generate_screen_from_text` → ✅ 200, generates real screen in ~40s\n  - Screenshot and HTML generated for project `9405789793801490511` (\"Bảng điều khiển\")\n- [x] **Listed all Stitch projects** for the user's account (27+ projects including \"Bảng điều khiển\", \"AHV Driving Training UI System\", etc.)\n- [x] **Updated backup MCP config** to use new wrapper: `command: \"node\"`, `args: [\"/root/.openclaw/mcp-stitch-key/server.mjs\"]`, `env: {\"STITCH_API_KEY\": \"AQ.Ab8RN6JCkRGaOOCFCgEm4hmzRy2RNmuoMBgzDB_qjHMxrEEruA\"}`\n- [x] **Validated backup**: valid JSON, 34 agents, 34 Telegram accounts, MCP config correct.\n- [x] **Pre-applied live config backup**: `openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12-PRE-APPLY` saved before applying.\n- [x] **Applied backup to live**: `cp /root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12 /root/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n- [x] **Restarted gateway** via `openclaw gateway restart`\n- [x] Updated `memory/2026-04-12.md` with all findings.\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Verify MCP Stitch works via OpenClaw** — spawn `stitch-design` agent to test the full MCP chain after gateway restart.\n\n### Blocked\n- Agent-to-group communication architecture decision still pending.\n- `stitch-connect` skill needs correction to document API key limitations for read-only vs write operations.\n- `stitch-loop` skill prompts should be kept under ~40s to avoid OpenClaw MCP timeout.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **`thinkingDefault` is the correct config key**: Confirmed from schema inspection.\n- **`DEV` is primary, `TroLy` is fallback**: User designated DEV for orchestration/coordinating agents, TroLy for coding agents.\n- **Backup-first workflow**: All changes go into backup; live file unchanged until user confirmation.\n- **`allowAgents` accepts only agent IDs, not tool names**: Corrected.\n- **`sessions_spawn runtime=\"subagent\"` does not support `streamTo`**: Valid fields documented.\n- **`requireMention: false` in backup for group `-5212380728`**: Enables all bots to respond without explicit @mention.\n- **Daily briefing at 5:00 AM UTC+7**: Cron expression `0 5 * * *` with `tz: \"Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh\"`.\n- **`username` field invalid in TelegramAccountConfig schema**: Must be removed from all account entries. Telegram resolves username automatically from `botToken` via getMe API.\n- **`crons` key invalid at root level**: Not supported in installed OpenClaw version (2026.4.9).\n- **MCP Stitch works via TWO methods**:\n  1. **OAuth** (service account): Full access including `generate_screen_from_text`, ~17-90s per generation.\n  2. **API Key** (new method, simpler): Works for read ops AND `generate_screen_from_text` with the NEW key. Tested ✅.\n- **MCP Stitch endpoint**: `https://stitch.googleapis.com/mcp`\n- **Stitch generation time with new API key**: ~40s (prompt \"Mobile dashboard\" → dashboard screen with screenshot + HTML)\n- **Wrapper approach**: Custom Node.js ESM stdio MCP server at `/root/.openclaw/mcp-stitch-key/server.mjs` replaces `npx stitch-mcp` for API key auth.\n- **API key saved securely**: `/root/.openclaw/mcp-stitch-key/.env` (chmod 600).\n- **`stitch-connect` skill limitation**: Uses `X-Goog-Api-Key` header — only reliable for read operations. For `generate_screen_from_text`, use the MCP wrapper or OAuth approach.\n- **Stitch model options**: `GEMINI_3_FLASH` (default, faster) or `GEMINI_3_1_PRO` (higher quality).\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Verify MCP Stitch via OpenClaw**: Spawn `stitch-design` agent and test `generate_screen_from_text` through OpenClaw's MCP client.\n2. **Test gateway stability**: Check logs after restart for any schema errors.\n3. **Fix duplicate Telegram bot tokens**: `senior-architect_bot` ↔ `senior-backend_bot`; `stitch-loop_bot` ↔ `typescript-reviewer_bot`.\n4. **Rotate exposed Telegram bot tokens** via BotFather.\n5. **Optimize `stitch-loop` skill prompts**: Keep under ~40s to stay within OpenClaw MCP timeout (~60s).\n6. **Fix `stitch-connect` skill**: Document API key limitation, or update to use MCP wrapper.\n7. **Decide agent-to-group communication architecture**: Each agent speaks directly in group vs. master-orchestrator as sole spokesperson.\n8. **Test the 2 cron jobs**: progress report at 5-min intervals and daily briefing at 5:00 AM UTC+7.\n\n## Critical Context\n- Live config: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n- Pre-apply backup: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12-PRE-APPLY`\n- Backup config: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12`\n- Active Telegram group: `-5212380728`\n- User Telegram ID: `6053576134`\n- OpenClaw version: **2026.4.9** (installed at `/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/`)\n- OpenClaw logs: `/tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-12.log`, `/tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-11.log`\n- **MCP Stitch wrapper**: `/root/.openclaw/mcp-stitch-key/server.mjs` (ESM, Node.js)\n- **MCP Stitch API key**: `AQ.Ab8RN6JCkRGaOOCFCgEm4hmzRy2RNmuoMBgzDB_qjHMxrEEruA` (saved in `/root/.openclaw/mcp-stitch-key/.env`)\n- Stitch MCP endpoint: `https://stitch.googleapis.com/mcp`\n- Stitch MCP auth (new): `X-Goog-Api-Key: <key>` header + `?key=<key>` query param\n- Stitch MCP auth (old): `Authorization: Bearer <gcloud-auth-token>` + `X-Goog-User-Project: agent-stitch` (OAuth)\n- GCP service account: `agent-sti@agent-stitch.iam.gserviceaccount.com` in project `agent-stitch`\n- Known Stitch project IDs: `9405789793801490511` (\"Bảng điều khiển\"), `16861969867502723363` (\"AHV Driving Training UI System\"), and 25+ others.\n- MCP wrapper timeout: 120s (to accommodate Stitch generation times of 17-90s)\n- `stitch-connect` skill path: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/stitch-design/skills/stitch-connect/SKILL.md`\n- `stitch-loop` skill path: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/stitch-loop/skills/stitch-loop/SKILL.md`\n- All 34 Telegram bots confirmed as `member` in group `-5212380728` with real usernames confirmed via `getMe` API.\n- **Gateway restarted** with new config at approximately 05:46 UTC.\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser (Khương Nịnh) asked whether the new setup/config has been applied to `openclaw.json`.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Assistant confirmed the gateway is **running** (PIDs 354821, 354856)\n- **3 Stitch MCP wrapper instances** are running (`node /root/.openclaw/mcp-stitch-key/server.mjs`)\n- **openclaw.json was updated** with new config, gateway restarted via systemd\n- Telegram channel had transient 503 errors on startup (separate issue)\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe assistant was in the middle of **diagnosing why Stitch MCP is still returning timeouts** (`MCP error -32001: Request timed out`) on `stitch__generate_screen_from_text` calls, despite the new wrapper being loaded. The investigation revealed:\n- The wrapper is indeed spawned by the gateway\n- Recent errors at `7:58 UTC` have **different project IDs** than the earlier successful test, suggesting requests from a separate `stitch-design` agent session\n- The assistant was about to test the wrapper directly with an API key to verify it responds correctly\n\n<read-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/skills/master-orchestrator/SKILL.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/stitch-design/skills/stitch-connect/SKILL.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/stitch-loop/skills/stitch-loop/SKILL.md\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/access-B1I79MZ7.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/bot-ClNJQIfx.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/channel-94kVnXDM.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/channel-policy-CrbswhIK.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/group-access-hrkZp9Cg.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/plugin-sdk/src/config/types.telegram.d.ts\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/2026-04-12.md\n</modified-files>",
