        "summary": "## Goal\n- Get the 34-agent OpenClaw ecosystem stable and operational.\n- Fix Stitch MCP end-to-end (generate screens via AI).\n- Set up automatic progress reporting (5-minute intervals, daily 5AM UTC+7).\n- **NEW:** Connect Confluence MCP (dtlx.atlassian.net) and GitLab MCP (gitlab.com) to the ecosystem.\n- **NEW:** Ensure all agents can access GitLab for code review, CI/CD, and documentation operations.\n- **NEW:** Debug and fix group session unresponsiveness.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- All config changes go to backup first, user confirms before applying live.\n- Each agent should have its own Telegram bot identity.\n- Timezone: UTC+7 (Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh).\n- Daily briefing: 5:00 AM UTC+7.\n- All 34 bots must be in group `-5212380728`.\n- Real Telegram bot tokens were exposed — must be rotated.\n- Do not restart gateway until user explicitly confirms.\n- **NEW:** MCP servers must use embedded credentials (gateway doesn't pass `env` to subprocesses).\n\n## Progress\n\n### Done\n- [x] All config updates (thinkingDefault, models, per-agent settings, 34 Telegram bots, MCP Stitch wrapper).\n- [x] **Stitch MCP wrapper root cause + fix**: Gateway doesn't pass `env` vars to MCP wrapper processes → `STITCH_API_KEY` was empty → all Stitch calls failed. Fix: embedded API key `AQ.Ab8RN6JCkRGaOOCFCgEm4hmzRy2RNmuoMBgzDB_qjHMxrEEruA` directly in `/root/.openclaw/mcp-stitch-key/server.mjs`.\n- [x] **Wrapper updated with async polling**: Submit request → poll every 5s → return final result. Max wait 300s. Handles Stitch generation times of 17-90s.\n- [x] Direct wrapper test: `generate_screen_from_text` ✅, screenshot + HTML returned, ~62 seconds.\n- [x] **Cron jobs created and working** (via `cron` tool with `sessionTarget: \"isolated\"`):\n  - `ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` — 5p Progress Report: every 5 min → group `-5212380728` ✅ (2 successful runs, `lastStatus: \"ok\"`, `lastDelivered: true`)\n  - `53c5832a-eecc-4d6b-a4c3-d1b78a430dca` — Daily Briefing: 05:00 AM UTC+7 → group `-5212380728` ✅\n- [x] **Fixed stale cron job prompt**: Old prompt incorrectly reported stale bugs. Updated to accurate current-status prompt. Fixed `5p Progress Report` cron job via `cron(action=\"update\", jobId=\"ed2d0b5d-...\")`.\n- [x] **System session/memory cleanup**: 43 sessions → 3 sessions kept. All luxury-ecom, team-orchestrator, and stale agent sessions removed from `sessions.json` + deleted ~70 `.jsonl` transcript files. Removed stale `.reset.*`, `.tmp`, `.lock` files. Updated `MEMORY.md` with active sessions list. Short-term recall cleaned.\n- [x] **Confluence MCP connected** (`https://dtlx.atlassian.net/wiki`, user `ninhkhuongpl7`, account active). Confirmed 10+ spaces including `AW` (AHV Work), `AC` (AI CMS), `OTLXPA1` (Đào tạo lái xe). Config added to `mcp.servers.confluence` → gateway restart required. Confluence MCP processes running after gateway restart.\n- [x] **GitLab MCP connected** (gitlab.com, user `ninhkhuongpl7`, 6 groups). Token `glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65` verified valid. Groups: `ahv-dtlx`, `ahv-works/ahv-hrm`, `ahv-landing-page`, `ahv-landing-page/ahv-landing-page-v2`, plus personal groups.\n- [x] **Custom GitLab MCP wrapper written** at `/root/.openclaw/mcp-gitlab/server.mjs` (ESM, MCP SDK) with 13 tools: `gitlab_search_projects`, `gitlab_get_project`, `gitlab_list_branches`, `gitlab_create_branch`, `gitlab_get_file`, `gitlab_create_or_update_file`, `gitlab_list_issues`, `gitlab_create_issue`, `gitlab_list_merge_requests`, `gitlab_create_merge_request`, `gitlab_list_pipelines`, `gitlab_trigger_pipeline`, `gitlab_list_commits`. GitLab PAT embedded directly in wrapper code (gateway doesn't pass `env` to MCP subprocesses). SDK installed locally at `/root/.openclaw/mcp-gitlab/node_modules/@modelcontextprotocol/sdk`.\n- [x] **MCP config schema fixed**: `mcpServers` at root level causes `\"Unrecognized key: mcpServers\"` error. Correct placement is `mcp.servers` (not `mcpServers`). Updated `openclaw.json` accordingly.\n- [x] **Gateway env updated**: Added `GITLAB_TOKEN` and `GITLAB_URL` to root-level `env` section of `openclaw.json` for all agents to use with git clone.\n- [x] **Multiple gateway restarts** performed. Tracked down issue: multiple `openclaw-gateway` processes accumulating (PID 356713, 358706, etc.). Proper kill + start sequence now established.\n- [x] **Package corrections**: `@gitlab-org/mcp-gitlab` package does not exist on npm. `@modelcontextprotocol/server-gitlab` is deprecated (as of 2025.4.25). Used custom wrapper instead.\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Test GitLab MCP tools end-to-end through OpenClaw** — wrapper processes running but not yet verified accessible to agents.\n- [ ] **Debug group session stuck** — `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728` showing context overflow + `FallbackSummaryError: All models failed (2)` + LLM timeouts. Session unresponsive to `sessions_send` (timeout). Gateway restart needed to clear.\n- [ ] **Verify agents can access GitLab via `GITLAB_TOKEN` env var** — token added to `env` section but gateway may not inject env vars into exec subprocesses. May need to also embed in agent workspace configs or per-agent `env` overrides.\n- [ ] **Gateway systemd reload**: Need to properly reload gateway to pick up all config changes (confluence MCP, gitlab MCP, env vars).\n\n### Blocked\n- [x] ~~Gateway doesn't pass `env` to MCP wrappers~~ → Fixed by embedding API key in wrapper code.\n- [x] ~~Cron `sessionTarget: \"main\"` not supported for channel delivery~~ → Fixed by using `sessionTarget: \"isolated\"`.\n- [x] ~~Stale cron job prompts~~ → Fixed by updating via `cron` tool.\n- [x] ~~GitLab MCP npm package name~~ → Fixed: `@gitlab-org/mcp-gitlab` doesn't exist. `@modelcontextprotocol/server-gitlab` deprecated. Custom wrapper written.\n- [x] ~~`mcpServers` at root level rejected~~ → Fixed: moved to `mcp.servers`.\n- [ ] **GitLab `env` injection to agents**: `env` section in `openclaw.json` may not inject into exec subprocesses where agents run `git clone`. Not yet verified.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **`sessionTarget: \"isolated\"` required for channel delivery**: `cron channel delivery config is only supported for sessionTarget=\"isolated\"`. Jobs with `sessionTarget: \"main\"` get rejected.\n- **Embedded API key over env injection**: Gateway's MCP server spawning doesn't pass `env` from config to child processes. Embedding key in wrapper code is the reliable approach.\n- **Async polling for long Stitch generation**: Wrapper now submits → polls every 5s → returns final result. This keeps the gateway's MCP request open for up to 300s.\n- **Cron tool over CLI**: `openclaw cron` CLI hangs in exec (interactive TTY required). `cron` tool (via `sessions_send` or direct agent call) works reliably.\n- **`DEV` is primary model, `TroLy` is fallback**: DEV for orchestration/research agents; TroLy for coding agents.\n- **Custom GitLab MCP wrapper over npm package**: `@modelcontextprotocol/server-gitlab` is deprecated; wrote own wrapper for full control.\n- **`mcp.servers` not `mcpServers`**: Gateway config schema rejects `mcpServers` at root level. Correct key is `mcp.servers`.\n- **GitLab agents use `git clone` directly**: Not through MCP tools → need `GITLAB_TOKEN` injected into exec environment.\n- **Confluence MCP via `confluence-mcp-server` npm**: Community package `confluence-mcp-server@1.1.0` supports Cloud Basic Auth. Uses `CONF_MODE=cloud`, `CONF_BASE_URL`, `CONF_USERNAME`, `CONF_TOKEN`, `CONF_DEFAULT_SPACE`.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Restart gateway** to pick up all pending config changes (env vars, MCP servers).\n2. **Test GitLab token env injection**: Verify agents can `git clone` with embedded token. If not working, embed token in each agent workspace's execution environment.\n3. **Clear stuck group session**: Send abort or restart gateway to unstick `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728`.\n4. **Test Confluence and GitLab MCP tools** through a real agent session.\n5. **Rotate exposed Telegram bot tokens** via BotFather (still pending from earlier).\n6. **Verify Stitch MCP end-to-end** through OpenClaw's MCP client.\n7. **Update `stitch-connect` skill** to document MCP wrapper usage.\n\n## Critical Context\n- Live config: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json` (keys: `env`, `mcp.servers`)\n- Pre-apply backup: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12-PRE-APPLY`\n- Backup config: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12`\n- Confluence backup: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12-CONFLUENCE`\n- Active Telegram group: `-5212380728`\n- User Telegram ID: `6053576134`\n- OpenClaw version: **2026.4.9** (`/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/`)\n- OpenClaw logs: `/tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-12.log`\n- **MCP Stitch wrapper**: `/root/.openclaw/mcp-stitch-key/server.mjs` (ESM, with embedded API key + async polling)\n- **MCP Stitch API key**: `AQ.Ab8RN6JCkRGaOOCFCgEm4hmzRy2RNmuoMBgzDB_qjHMxrEEruA`\n- **MCP Confluence config**: `command: \"npx\"`, `args: [\"-y\", \"confluence-mcp-server\"]`, env: `CONF_MODE=cloud`, `CONF_BASE_URL=https://dtlx.atlassian.net/wiki`, `CONF_USERNAME=ninhkhuongpl7@gmail.com`, `CONF_TOKEN=<atlassian-api-token>`, `CONF_DEFAULT_SPACE=AW`\n- **MCP GitLab wrapper**: `/root/.openclaw/mcp-gitlab/server.mjs` (ESM, MCP SDK, embedded GitLab PAT)\n- **GitLab PAT**: `glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65`\n- **GitLab groups accessible**: `ahv-dtlx` (private), `ahv-works/ahv-hrm`, `ahv-landing-page`, `ahv-landing-page/ahv-landing-page-v2`, plus personal groups\n- **Stitch MCP endpoint**: `https://stitch.googleapis.com/mcp`\n- **Confluence spaces**: `AW` (AHV Work), `AC` (AI CMS), `OTLXPA1` (Đào tạo lái xe - Phúc An), 8+ personal spaces\n- Cron job IDs:\n  - 5p Progress Report: `ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` ✅ running, lastStatus \"ok\", prompt updated\n  - Daily Briefing 5AM UTC+7: `53c5832a-eecc-4d6b-a4c3-d1b78a430dca` ✅ scheduled for 2026-04-13 05:00 UTC+7\n- **Group session stuck**: `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728` has context overflow + model failures. Unresponsive to `sessions_send`. Needs gateway restart.\n- **Current MCP servers**: `stitch` (embedded key), `confluence` (npx), `gitlab` (custom wrapper at `/root/.openclaw/mcp-gitlab/server.mjs`)\n- **Gateway env vars**: `AHVHOLDING_API_KEY`, `GITLAB_TOKEN`, `GITLAB_URL` now in `openclaw.json` `env` section\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser asked to fix the system (\"sửa hộ tôi\" - Vietnamese for \"fix it for me\").\n\n## Early Progress\n- Assistant checked system status via `ps aux`, `systemctl status`, and log analysis\n- Found openclaw-gateway process running (PID 364880, 84.4% CPU)\n- Systemd service shows **failed** status since 07:37:53 UTC\n- Log reveals root cause: \"already running under systemd; waiting 5000ms before retrying startup\" — duplicate process conflict\n- Recent logs show WebSocket handshake timeouts and Telegram network/fallback issues\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe system has a process conflict where the gateway is running directly but systemd can't manage it properly, plus network connectivity problems causing connection failures. The suffix likely contains further diagnostic steps or attempted fixes for this state.\n\n<read-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/skills/master-orchestrator/SKILL.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/stitch-design/skills/stitch-connect/SKILL.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/stitch-loop/skills/stitch-loop/SKILL.md\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/access-B1I79MZ7.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/bot-ClNJQIfx.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/channel-94kVnXDM.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/channel-policy-CrbswhIK.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/group-access-hrkZp9Cg.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/plugin-sdk/src/config/types.telegram.d.ts\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/root/.openclaw/mcp-gitlab/server.mjs\n/root/.openclaw/mcp-stitch-key/server.mjs\n/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12-CONFLUENCE\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/MEMORY.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/2026-04-12.md\n</modified-files>",
